  "body": "I'm not sure about the underlying reason, but it seems to be related to the `error` field in ether's error message, which is something like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\n... errror={\"stackTrace\":[{\"type\":4,\"sourceReference\":\r\n{\"function\":\"revertsWithoutReason\",\"contract\":\"Foo\",\"sourceName\":\"contracts/Foo.sol\",\r\n\"sourceContent\":\"// SPDX-License-Identifier: ...continues\",\r\n\"line\":8,\"range\":[141,155]},\"message\":{\"value\":{\"type\":\"Buffer\",\"data\":[]}},\r\n\"isInvalidOpcodeError\":false}],\"data\":\"0x\"} ...\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen the contract is large, this causes the output to be super hard to read (see #3444)",
